Detailed Description

The base class for planning groups.

Base class to run as a plugin for other classes to be definded later.

Attention
Documentation will be an ongoing process with more comments filled in as methods are implemented.
Some methods and variables were found in path_planner.py but had no implemtation. I've listed them here in case we want to implement them.
  • std::map<> group_controllers_; NOTE not implemented in path_planner.py
  • std::map<> trajectory_poses_; NOTE not implemented in path_planner.py
  • std::map<std::string, EndEffectorHelper> end_effector_display_; // TODO this is in end_effector_helper.py in RIT
  • std::map<std::string, srdf::Model::EndEffector> end_effector_map_;
  • std::map<> command_topics_; NOTE not implemented in path_planner.py
  • std::map<std::string, ??> gripper_action_; FIXME this doesn't seem to be implemented, objects never get inserted
  • std::map<std::string, actionlib::SimpleActionClient<robot_interaction_tools::GripperCommandAction> > gripper_client_; // FIXME this action isn't defined
  • std::map<> bridge_topic_map_;

void PlannerInterface::initialize ( std::string  robot_name,
std::string  config_file,
std::string  robot_description = "robot_description" 
)
pure virtual

A pure virtual method for all subs to implement.

Initialize the planning class with robot details. Setup callbacks. Ready publishing topics.

Parameters
robot_namethe name of the robot to use in topics and loading SRDF files
config_filefile to parse models from
robot_descriptionoptional. load discription file from rosparam server
Returns
none
Attention
We could leave the param field empty as this is a pure virtual and instead have a private method or use theconstructor for initialization
